		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message28384593">If there is one thing that I love about this anime, it's the climactic singing scene halfway through the film. We often praise Ghibli for their talent in animating stuff, but this scene is the one in which their talent is truly put to use. The scene slowly builds the climax, using the three old men's arrival to boost the scene, starting with the tambourine only, then introducing more instruments as the scene goes. Adding to the climax is Shizuku opening up with body language more and more dynamic, all animated with a realism on par with the very best of the medium. <!--link--><a href="http://www.dailymotion.com/video/x3encn_si-tu-tends-l-oreille-country-road_fun" rel="nofollow">Here's the scene, so you can check that for yourself. :)</a></div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
